[In the past 24 hours, India (131 893), Brazil (89 293), the USA (80 161), and Turkey (55 941) have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 13 904 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 7 Apr 2021 to late 8 Apr 2021). Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (12 countries) include India, Brazil, the USA, Turkey, Poland (27 899), Germany (24 257), Argentina (23 683), Iran (22 586), Ukraine (19 419), Poland (14 913), Italy (17 207), and Columbia (12 464). A total of 67 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 39 of the 67 countries are from the European region, 10 are from the Americas region, 9 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 3 are from the South East Asia region, 3 are from the Western Pacific region, and 3 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 7.3%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 0.8%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 2.3% increase in daily reported cases and a 7.2% increase in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily report counted over 800 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 134.51 million cumulative reported cases and over 2.91 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
